Copyright (c) 2026 Richard Fossland. All rights reserved.

SundayRec is source-available software. The full source code is published
on GitHub for transparency, security review, and community collaboration —
but it is not open-source under any OSI-approved definition.


PERMITTED USE
-------------

The following uses are permitted free of charge, provided that this
license and all copyright notices remain intact in every copy of the
source code:

  1. Reading and inspecting the source code for the purpose of
     understanding how SundayRec works, evaluating it before purchase,
     or learning from its implementation.

  2. Reporting bugs, suggesting improvements, and contributing patches
     through the project's GitHub issue tracker and pull request system.
     By submitting a contribution you grant the copyright holder a
     perpetual, royalty-free license to incorporate it into SundayRec
     under this license.

  3. Building and running SundayRec from source on your own computer
     for personal, private use.

  4. Use of the compiled official binaries by individuals and by
     non-profit religious organisations (congregations, parishes,
     dioceses, missions and similar) on their own infrastructure for
     the purpose of recording, editing and publishing their own
     services. This permission extends regardless of the
     organisation's size or budget, provided the use itself is
     non-commercial.

     Concrete examples of PERMITTED use under this clause:

       a. A small village church recording the weekly Sunday service
          for its own podcast feed, free of charge to listeners.
       b. A large megachurch with thousands of members recording its
          services and posting them to YouTube or Spotify, free of
          charge to listeners.
       c. A diocese or denomination using SundayRec across multiple
          parishes for their own services.
       d. A volunteer organisation recording sermons for shut-in
          members of their congregation.

     Concrete examples of NON-PERMITTED use under this clause (which
     require a commercial agreement — see below):

       e. A Christian radio station that monetises its broadcasts
          through paid sponsorships, donor benefits tied to access,
          or paid subscriptions.
       f. A media company that records services for paying client
          churches as a paid service offering.
       g. A conference organiser charging admission and using
          SundayRec to produce the official recording.
       h. Any organisation re-selling the SundayRec-produced output
          as part of a paid product (e.g. paid courses, paid streaming
          subscriptions, DVDs, archived podcast paywalls).

     The deciding factor is NOT the organisation's size, tax status,
     or revenue — it is whether the use of SundayRec itself is part
     of a commercial revenue stream. If unsure, contact
     hello@sundayrec.com for a written determination at no cost.


PROHIBITED USE
--------------

Without prior written permission from the copyright holder, you may NOT:

  1. Redistribute the source code or compiled binaries, in original or
     modified form, whether for free or for a fee.

  2. Use SundayRec, in source or binary form, for any commercial
     purpose. "Commercial purpose" includes — but is not limited to —
     selling the software, charging for access to it, offering it as a
     hosted or managed service, bundling it with a paid product, or
     using it as part of a for-profit service offering.

  3. Create and distribute modified versions or derivative works.

  4. Remove or alter copyright notices, license terms, trademarks, or
     branding (including the SundayRec name and logo).

  5. Use the SundayRec name, logo, or trademarks to endorse or promote
     any product or service derived from this software.


